events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron passed for 208 yards and two touchdowns and Alabama reached the end zone on its first three possessions in a 38-7 victory over Mississippi State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bama rides fast start to rout of Mississippi State

events.name: Florida Gators at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Georgia (No. 10 BCS, No. 12 AP) stuffed Florida (No. 2 BCS, No. 3 AP) from every angle, forcing six turnovers in a 17-9 victory Saturday that left them on the cusp of making the Southeastern Conference title game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia upends sloppy Gators

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Collin Klein accounted for four touchdowns, Arthur Brown returned an interception 37 yards for another score and Kansas State roughed up Texas Tech 55-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: K-State clubs Texas Tech

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Kenjon Barner rushed for 104 yards and two touchdowns, and Oregon (No. 4 BCS, No. 2 AP) easily took care of Colorado 70-14 on Saturday in advance of next weekend's Pac-12 showdown with USC (No. 9 BCS, No. 10 AP).
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Ducks score 56 by half, rout Buffaloes

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Everett Golson threw for 177 yards and plunged in for the decisive 1-yard touchdown in the fourth quarter, Manti Te'o bolstered his Heisman Trophy candidacy with a late interception and Notre Dame beat Oklahoma 30-13.
headlines.shortLinkText: ND tops Oklahoma to stay unbeaten

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Washington beat Oregon State 20-17 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington sends No. 7 Oregon St. to first loss

events.name: USC Trojans at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Matt Scott had 469 total yards and accounted for four touchdowns, helping Arizona overcome a huge day by Southern California's Marqise Lee to beat the Trojans (No. 9 USC, No. 10 AP) 39-36 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: USC gets upset by Arizona

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: EJ Manuel tossed two touchdown passes and Devonta Freeman ran for two more scores to lead Florida State (No. 12 BCS, No. 11 AP) to a 48-7 victory over Duke on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manuel's 2 TDs help No. 12 FSU roll Duke

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw threw three touchdowns and ran for another, and South Carolina (No. 13 BCS, No. 17 AP) overcame the loss of tailback Marcus Lattimore for a 38-35 victory over Tennessee on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina loses Lattimore, outlasts Tennessee

events.name: Kent State Golden Flashes at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Defensive end Mark Fackler returned his second interception 25 yards for a touchdown, and Kent State forced five other turnovers in stunning No. 18 Rutgers 35-23 Saturday for its biggest win since its first game in 1920.
headlines.shortLinkText: First defeats: No. 15 Rutgers

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Ed Reynolds returned an interception for a touchdown, and Stanford (No. 17 BCS, No. 19 AP) sacked Jeff Tuel 10 times to overcome a sloppy offensive effort in a 24-17 victory over Washington State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford collects 10 sacks to upend Wazzu

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel ran for three touchdowns and passed for two more -- all in a little more than a half -- and Texas A&M (No. 20 BCS, No. 22 AP) beat struggling Auburn 63-21 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manziel, Texas A&ampM rout slumping Auburn

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Wyoming Cowboys

venue.fullName: Jonah Field at War Memorial Stadium

headlines.description: D.J. Harper rushed for 105 yards and two touchdowns to lead No. 21 Boise State past Wyoming 45-14 Saturday for its seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harper, No. 21 Boise State run past Wyoming

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Ameer Abdullah ran for 101 yards and a touchdown and Nebraska took control of the Big Ten Legends Division with a 23-9 victory over No. 20 Michigan on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nebraska knocks off injured Robinson, Michigan

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Case McCoy hit D.J. Grant with a 1-yard touchdown pass with 12 seconds to play, capping a 70-yard drive in the final 2 minutes and lifting Texas past Kansas 21-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCoy, Texas rally past Kansas

events.name: Ohio Bobcats at Miami (OH) RedHawks

headlines.description: Ohio gambled by going for one more play instead of a tying field goal, and Tyler Tettleton was sacked as time ran out, preserving Miami of Ohio's 23-20 upset over the Bobcats on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami (OH) deals No. 24 Ohio 1st loss of season

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Andrew Maxwell threw a 12-yard touchdown pass to Bennie Fowler in overtime, giving Michigan State a 16-13 victory and snapping Wisconsin's 21-game home winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mich. St. wins in OT to snap Wisconsin's run

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Kain Colter scored three rushing touchdowns and threw for another score as Northwestern defeated Iowa 28-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colter leads Northwestern past sloppy Iowa

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Missouri got touchdowns off all three of Kentucky's lost fumbles and quarterback James Franklin presided over a strong finish in a reserve role as the Tigers earned a long-delayed first win in their debut SEC season with a 33-10 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mizzou recovers 3 fumbles to earn 1st SEC win

events.name: Temple Owls at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Ray Graham rushed for two touchdowns and caught another as Pittsburgh rolled over Temple 47-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham (3 TDs), Pittsburgh roll past Temple

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Nate Sudfeld came off Indiana's bench to throw for two touchdowns, and the Hoosiers defense had seven sacks and a pair of key turnovers in a 31-17 win at Illinois on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana snaps 11-game Big Ten losing streak

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Gio Bernard returned a punt 74 yards for the go-ahead touchdown with 13 seconds left, helping North Carolina stun rival North Carolina State 43-35 to end a five-year losing streak in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC returns late punt for TD, stuns rival NC St.

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Chase Rettig completed a 14-yard touchdown pass to Johnathan Coleman with 52 seconds left to give Boston College a 20-17 victory over Maryland on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: BC scores late, defeats Maryland

headlines.description: Ka'imi Fairbairn kicked a 33-yard field goal as the game ended and UCLA escaped with a 45-43 victory over Arizona State on Saturday.

events.name: BYU Cougars at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Jamaal Williams scored four touchdowns, quarterback Riley Nelson accounted for two TDs, and Brigham Young snapped a two-game losing streak with a 41-17 victory over Georgia Tech on Saturday.
